  <datafield tag="545" ind1="0" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Paul Heaton was actively involved in political campaigns dealing with human rights ordinances in the cities of Ypsilanti and Traverse City, Michigan. He served as co-chair of the Ypsilanti Campaign for Equality and the Traverse City Campaign Against Discrimination, organizations that sought to fight anti-gay initiatives in relation to these ordinances.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1="2" ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The collection, organized by campaign, includes correspondence, political documents, flyers and published articles as well as materials detailing fundraising efforts and election strategy. The collection primarily documents the efforts of the Ypsilanti Campaign for Equality and the Traverse City Campaign Against Discrimination, but includes general information about the campaigns as well. The collection also includes Heaton's training materials for a Michigan Equality program detailing how to organize a successful human rights ordinance political campaign.</subfield>
  </datafield>
